FBIS4-36714 "drnes113_p_94001" FBIS-NES-94-113 Daily Report 9 Jun 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Rabbani Government Proposes Peace Formula Rabbani Government Proposes Peace Formula BK0906101594 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 GMT 9 Jun 94 BK0906101594 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network Urdu BFN [Text] In Afghanistan, President Borhanoddin Rabbani's government has submitted a two-point peace formula for the restoration of durable peace in the country. The formula provides for the ceasing forthwith of rocket attacks on Kabul, honoring the cease-fire, and opening up all highways leading to Kabul. It also proposes the setting up of an authoritative nongovernmental commission to initiate work on the Representative Council and Grand Assembly.
